The paper proposes a method to improve the robustness of federated learning against local data corruption, which is a common problem in machine learning. The proposed method involves collaborative machine teaching using trusted instances, which is a combination of machine learning and data privacy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
